PASSWORD POLICY
================================================================================
Company: Ahmnest SecureTech Solution
Effective Date: [Date]
Version: 1.0
================================================================================

1. PURPOSE
================================================================================
This policy establishes requirements for creating, managing, and protecting
passwords used to access Ahmnest SecureTech Solution's systems and data.

2. SCOPE
================================================================================
This policy applies to all users with access to company systems, applications,
and data.

3. PASSWORD REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================
3.1 Complexity Requirements:
| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Minimum Length | 12 characters |
| Character Types | Upper, Lower, Numbers, Special |
| Password History | 12 previous passwords remembered |
| Maximum Age | 90 days |
| Account Lockout | 5 attempts, 30-minute lockout |

3.2 Strong Password Examples:
- CorrectHorseBatteryStaple!
- Tr0ub4dour&3#Horse
- B@tteryH0rseSt@ple!2025

3.3 Weak Passwords (Prohibited):
- Password123
- CompanyName2025
- 123456789
- qwerty

4. MULTI-FACTOR AUTHENTICATION (MFA)
================================================================================
MFA is required for:
- All administrative accounts
- All remote access
- Email and collaboration platforms
- Cloud services and applications
- VPN access

5. PASSWORD MANAGEMENT BEST PRACTICES
================================================================================
- Never share passwords with anyone
- Don't write down passwords
- Don't reuse passwords across systems
- Report suspected compromise immediately
- Use password manager (company-approved)

6. ENFORCEMENT
================================================================================
Non-compliance with this policy may result in access revocation and disciplinary
action up to and including termination.

================================================================================
